sameAnalysis.part_name: 这些动词均含"服从，听从"之意。
means: obey ： 一般用词，指服从或接受某种权威，或遵循某种原则而行事。
comply ： 指同意依从他人的愿望或请求，或遵守某种规则或顺应某种环境条件。
submit ： 指顺从或屈服于自己不能进一步抵制或抵抗的人或事物。

sameAnalysis.part_name: 这些动词均含"屈服，投降"之意。
means: submit ： 一般指放弃抵抗，愿意服从对方。
yield ： 含义相近，还指由于缺乏坚强的意志、力量和忍耐心，而屈从于他人的权势或控制。
surrender ： 指由于战败被迫投降或向战胜者或某种权势屈服。

entry.tran: 顺从;屈服;投降;被迫接受
entry.def: If you submit to something, you unwillingly allow something to be done to you, or you do what someone wants, for example because you are not powerful enough to resist.

example.ex: In desperation, Mrs. Jones submitted to an operation on her right knee to relieve the pain...
example.tran: 绝望之际，琼斯夫人只好同意在其右膝上做手术以减轻疼痛。

example.ex: If I submitted to their demands, they would not press the allegations.
example.tran: 如果那时我答应他们的要求，他们就不会坚持那些指控了。

entry.tran: 提交，递呈(建议、报告或请求)
entry.def: If you submit a proposal, report, or request to someone, you formally send it to them so that they can consider it or decide about it.

example.ex: They submitted their reports to the Chancellor yesterday...
example.tran: 他们昨天向财政大臣递交了报告。

example.ex: Head teachers yesterday submitted a claim for a 9 per cent pay rise.
example.tran: 校长们昨天提交了一份要求加薪 9%的声明。
